“Track a block of equal numbers with L.
Move R forward.
If value changes → set L = R (new block).
Longest block length = answer.”

⚡ Full Approach (Step-by-Step, No Code)
Step 1 — Use two pointers: L and R

L marks the start of the current block of identical numbers.

R moves across the array (0 → n-1).

Step 2 — Compare nums[L] and nums[R]

If they are equal → we remain inside the same subarray.

If they are different →
The previous block ended.
Set:

L = R


This starts a new block from position R.

Step 3 — Track the maximum block length

At each R:

current_length = R - L + 1
update max_length

Step 4 — Continue to the end

The answer is the largest length found.

