1. Inserting a word
🎯 Goal

Store a word letter by letter while reusing common prefixes.

🔍 How it works

• Start from the root (empty node)
• Move through each letter in order
• If a letter path doesn’t exist → create it
• Move forward until the last letter

⚡ At the last letter, mark:

“A complete word ends here.”

This is what the word flag represents.

🧠 Mental Map

“Walk letters → stop → stamp END OF WORD.”

2. Searching for a word
🎯 Goal

Confirm whether a full word exists — not just a prefix.

🔍 How it works

• Start from the root
• Follow the path of each letter
• If any letter is missing → word does not exist
• After the final letter, check:

⚡ Is this node marked as a word end?

✔ Yes → valid word
❌ No → only a prefix

🧠 Mental Map

“Path exists + word-end stamp → word found.”

3. Checking a prefix (startsWith)
🎯 Goal

Check whether any word starts with this prefix.

🔍 How it works

• Start from the root
• Walk through prefix letters
• If all letters exist in sequence → prefix exists

🚫 No need to check word ending

🧠 Mental Map

“Prefix only needs a path, not a destination.”

