@staticmethod
def build(nums, L, R):


🎯 Goal

Construct the full tree from the array.

🔍 How it works

• If L == R → leaf node
• Otherwise:

Split range in half

Build left child

Build right child

Sum = left.sum + right.sum

Key idea:

Build children first
Then compute parent


🧠 Mental Map

“Divide range.
Build children.
Combine results.”

❓ Why is build a static method?

Because:

• It does NOT use self
• Tree does not exist yet
• It creates and returns the first node

So it belongs to the class,
but doesn’t depend on an object.

Think:

“Factory method to create tree.”

