👉 Prim’s Algorithm – Min Heap (Priority Queue) (Cost + Edges Version)

Compute the Minimum Spanning Tree (MST) of a weighted undirected graph using a min-heap — and return both total cost and MST edges.

✨ Flashcard

“Start anywhere → always pick smallest edge connecting new node → grow tree → track parent to store edges.”

⚡ Full Explanation (Very Easy)
1️⃣ Build adjacency list

🎯 Goal

Store graph in a format that allows fast neighbor access.

🔍 How the code works (Line-by-Line)

adj = {i: [] for i in range(1, n+1)}

for u, v, w in edges:
    adj[u].append((v, w))
    adj[v].append((u, w))

Create dictionary for all nodes

Since MST is undirected, add both directions:

u → v

v → u

🧠 Mental Map

“Adjacency list = who is connected to whom, and at what cost.”

📦 Complexity

Time: O(E)
Space: O(V + E)

2️⃣ Initialize visited set

🎯 Goal

Track which nodes are already inside the MST.

🔍 How the code works

visited = set()

Empty set at start

When a node is added to MST → add to visited

🧠 Mental Map

“Visited = nodes already inside the growing tree.”

📦 Complexity

Time: O(1)
Space: O(V)

3️⃣ Initialize min-heap

🎯 Goal

Always pick the smallest edge that connects to a new node.

🔍 How the code works

minHeap = [(0, 1, -1)]   # (weight, node, parent)

Heap stores:

(weight, node, parent)

Start from node 1

Weight = 0 (first node has no incoming edge)

Parent = -1 (because it has no parent)

🧠 Mental Map

“Heap = all edges touching the current tree. Smallest one wins.”

Parent helps us remember:
👉 Who connected this node to the tree.

📦 Complexity

Initial push: O(1)
Each push/pop: O(log V)

4️⃣ Process nodes

🎯 Goal

Grow MST until all nodes are included.

🔍 How the code works

while minHeap and len(visited) < n:
    weight, node, parent = heapq.heappop(minHeap)

    if node in visited:
        continue

Pop smallest edge

If node already in MST → skip

This prevents cycles

🧠 Mental Map

“Heap may contain extra edges → ignore if node already taken.”

📦 Complexity

Total: O(E log V)

5️⃣ Add node to MST & push neighbors

🎯 Goal

Expand the tree from the new node.

🔍 How the code works

visited.add(node)
totalCost += weight

if parent != -1:
    mstEdges.append([parent, node])

for nei, w in adj[node]:
    if nei not in visited:
        heapq.heappush(minHeap, (w, nei, node))

Add node to visited

Add edge weight to total cost

If not starting node → store edge [parent, node]

Push outgoing edges into heap (if neighbor not visited)

🧠 Mental Map

“Take smallest edge → add new node → record edge → expose its edges → repeat.”

Tree keeps growing outward.

📦 Complexity

Each edge pushed once → O(E log V)

6️⃣ Return result

🎯 Goal

Return total weight AND edges of Minimum Spanning Tree.

return totalCost, mstEdges

🧠 Mental Map

“Tree built → structure + total cost ready.”

📦 Complexity

Time: O(1)
Space: O(1)

💡 Key Insight for Interviews

visited defines the growing tree

heap decides which edge to take next

Parent tracking allows storing MST structure

Skip if node already visited → prevents cycles

Works only for undirected connected graphs

